2. Experimental
2.1. Synthesis of the catalyst
Zn-MCM-41 was prepared as the following method. 1.2 g Zn(OH)2 was dissolved in 9.5 g 25 wt.% ammonia and then the mixture was added into 120 ml aqueous solution of 2.4 g cetyltrimethylammonium bromide.
Ten grams tetraethyl orthosilicate was added drop by drop in 15 min. After a few minutes, the formed white solids were filtered and dried in air at 90 8C. Calcining at 90 8C for 6 h gives Zn-MCM-41. The aqueous solution of Hg(NO3)2 and NH4NO3 was introduced into the mesopores of Zn-MCM-41 by wet impregnation. The incipient sample was dried at 70 8C in air and treated at 300 8C under argon stream to give Zn-MCM-41 supported HgO.
